menu "breadboard: bb_diag_http (bb_diag's aggregate HTTP surface)"

config BB_DIAG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_diag HTTP routes"
    default y
    depends on BB_DIAG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_http registers the legacy exact-route HTTP
        handlers: GET/DELETE /api/diag/boot, GET/DELETE /api/diag/panic,
        GET /api/diag/coredump, GET /api/diag/heap-check, GET /api/diag/tasks,
        and GET /api/diag/sockets. Relocated verbatim from bb_diag (B1-1153)
        -- same symbol name, same behavior, only ownership moved.

config BB_DIAG_PANIC_TRIGGER
    bool "Expose POST /api/diag/panic/trigger to force a panic (debug only)"
    default n
    depends on BB_DIAG_ROUTES
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_http exposes POST /api/diag/panic/trigger which
        deliberately dereferences a null pointer to force a LoadProhibited
        panic. Used to validate panic capture / coredump end-to-end on bench
        hardware without physically rebooting the device. NEVER ship to
        production: any unauthenticated caller can crash the firmware.

config BB_DIAG_SECTIONS
    bool "Build the generic /api/diag/* section registry (wildcard dispatch)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_sections_init() registers a GET /api/diag/*
        wildcard route dispatching to whichever section a caller has
        registered via bb_diag_register_section() (bb_diag). Independent of
        BB_DIAG_ROUTES (the legacy exact-route panic/coredump handlers) --
        this registry is a separate, generic seam that will eventually
        replace those handlers section by section. The portable registry
        itself (bb_diag_register_section, bb_diag) always builds regardless
        of this option; only this component's ESP-IDF wildcard-route
        dispatcher is gated.

# Dissolved in from the former bb_storage_http component (B1-1154, KB 1477)
# -- DELETE /api/diag/storage always builds (same posture as
# BB_DIAG_SECTIONS' portable registry above); this option gates ONLY the
# separate, destructive POST /api/diag/factory-reset route. Symbol name
# KEPT unchanged from its bb_storage_http-era name -- renaming would break
# any sdkconfig.defaults already setting it.
config BB_STORAGE_HTTP_FACTORY_RESET
    bool "Enable POST /api/diag/factory-reset route (full NVS wipe + deferred reboot)"
    default n
    help
      When enabled, registers POST /api/diag/factory-reset. A valid request
      body {"confirm":"factory-reset"} erases the entire "nvs" bb_storage
      backend (all namespaces), invalidates the RTC creds mirror so the
      restore-heal path cannot resurrect credentials, responds 202, then
      reboots after ~500 ms. Disabled by default because factory reset is a
      destructive operation that should be opt-in.

# Dissolved in from the former bb_log_http component (B1-1155, KB 1477) --
# symbol names KEPT unchanged from their bb_log_http-era names; renaming
# would break any sdkconfig.defaults already setting them.
config BB_LOG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_log HTTP routes (log-level GET/POST)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_http compiles the routes module that exposes
        GET /api/log/level and POST /api/log/level. Disable for headless
        logging-only consumers that compose bb_diag_http but don't want the
        routes wired.

        The structured log stream is served separately via bb_data/
        bb_data_http at GET /api/events?topic=log (see bb_log_event's
        "log" bb_data key, B1-1045).

config BB_LOG_SSE_KEEPALIVE_MS
    int "SSE keepalive interval (ms)"
    default 5000
    range 1000 60000
    depends on BB_LOG_ROUTES
    help
        Vestigial — the /api/logs SSE route has been retired. This symbol
        is kept to avoid build breakage on boards that still reference it
        via sdkconfig. It is unused.

endmenu
